<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-27T09:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-27T09:41:00-05:00" n="1530" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1530">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/46.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-27T08:00:00-06:41">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 27, 1914, 8 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s inquiry concerning French Brothers who were forced to
                                leave Monterey and who went to Havana via Brownsville, Texas, I
                                understand that no money was collected from them. I rendered them
                                considerable friendly assistance. I will inquire as to the matter of
                                school property and as to their return and report soon.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>